{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "7248ea5a-a12f-4e43-93ea-ebf6b1d1a8be",
    "name": "Personal Blogging",
    "description": "This collection covers the core API endpoints for a Personal Blogging platform, built around a local development server (http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/v1).\n\nIt is organized into two folders:\n\n**Auth** — Handles user identity and access:\n- `POST /auth/register` — Register a new user account\n- `POST /auth/login` — Authenticate an existing user and retrieve an access token\n\n**Posts** — Manages blog post content:\n- `GET /posts/` — Retrieve all published posts\n- `POST /posts/add` — Create a new blog post\n- `PUT /posts/{{post_id}}` — Update an existing post by ID\n- `DELETE /posts/{{post_id}}` — Delete a post by ID\n\nUse the Auth requests first to register or log in, then use the returned token to interact with the Posts endpoints.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "42740215"
  },
